title: Tween Workshop: The Making of a Woodblock Print
description:
Witness first-hand the beauty and complexity of Japanese woodblock prints. Explore traditional tools and papers as a teaching artist demonstrates transferring designs to a block, carving, and basic printing techniques. Come prepared to get your hands inky.

This workshop is designed for tweens on their own without an adult companion. Please enter your tween's name when asked for a registering adult. Thank you.

This program is currently at capacity. To be added to the waiting list, please email us at familyprograms@artic.edu with your name and the program that you’re interested in. Although it is not guaranteed, we will contact you upon availability.
